  "body": "In `0.4.4-develop.2016.10.26+commit.4f1b5d26.Linux.g++` it is impossible to look up events through inheritance if the base contract is explicitly specified.\n\nThe following code fails to compile:\n\n```\ncontract A {\n    event x();\n}\ncontract B is A {\n    function f() returns (uint) {\n        A.x();\n        return 1;\n    }\n}\n```\n\nwith\n\n```\n8:9: Error: Member \"x\" not found or not visible after argument-dependent lookup in type(contract A)\n        A.x();\n        ^-^\n```\n\nThis is very similar to #988.\n",
